<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,538,564]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet derives from the hastate-like lateral processes of the hypandrium (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 11" captionStartId="6.[151,273,1387,1411]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,217,1386]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,212,1412]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 11. Nepalomyia hastata sp. nov. Male. 8. Wing; 9. 3 rd antennal segment and arista, lateral view; 10. genitalia, lateral view; 11. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189017/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,181,577,603]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,341,615,641]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Comments.</emphasis>
The species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang et Saigusa" authorityName="Yang et Saigusa" box="[650,990,616,642]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Nepalomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis box="[650,769,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">N. furcata</emphasis>
(Yang 
<emphasis box="[859,880,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">et</emphasis>
Saigusa)
</taxonomicName>
in having the third antennal segment distinctly longer than wide, but it may be separated from the latter by the third antennal segment 
<number box="[1325,1362,654,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="1.2">1.2</number>
times longer than wide. In 
<taxonomicName box="[398,518,693,718]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Nepalomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis box="[398,518,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">N. furcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the third antennal segment is 
<number box="[883,920,693,719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times longer than wide (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" pageId="7" pageNumber="49" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T. (2001 a) The species of Neurigonella from China (Diptera: Empidoidea: Dolichopodidae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 37, 375 - 392." type="journal article" year="2001" yearSuffix="a">
Yang and Saigusa, 
<number box="[151,214,732,758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="2001.0">2001</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
